          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/15/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Follow-up DM, HTN. Post-COVID recovery check.
HPI: 45yo female here for chronic disease management. Recovered from COVID in January. Lingering fatigue but improving. No more cough or SOB. Asthma back to baseline.
A1c 8.2% — worsening. Admits poor dietary compliance during illness. Weight 198 (down from 200).
Assessment:
# DM2 (E11.9): A1c worsening. Increase glipizide to 10mg. Consider adding GLP-1 agonist. Diabetes educator referral.
# HTN (I10): BP 136/84 — improved. Continue current regimen.
# Hyperlipidemia (E11.69): LDL 128. Continue atorvastatin 40mg.
# Peripheral neuropathy (G62.9): Gabapentin helping. No dose change.
# Obesity (E66.01): Discussed weight management. GLP-1 agonist would address both DM and weight.
# Vitamin D deficiency: Recheck in 3 months.
Plan: Increase glipizide. Diabetes education referral. A1c in 3 months. Consider semaglutide at next visit. Shingrix dose 2 due (dose 1 was 09/2025). Mammogram overdue — ordered.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>01/05/2026</td><td>Gretchen Lockard, MD</td><td>Acute Visit</td><td>CC: Cough, sore throat, sinus pressure x 3 days
HPI: 45yo with DM presents with URI symptoms. Husband also ill. Yellow mucus, slight sinus pressure, sore throat, cough productive. No SOB at rest but mild with exertion.
COVID rapid: POSITIVE. Flu rapid: NEGATIVE.
PE: Fatigued but nontoxic. Bilateral TM normal. Nasal turbinates edematous. Pharynx no erythema. Shotty cervical adenopathy. Lungs: occasional expiratory wheeze bilaterally.
Assessment:
# COVID-19 (U07.1): Start Paxlovid — stop atorvastatin during treatment (interaction).
# Wheeze (R06.2): Start albuterol inhaler QID.
# Acute sinusitis (J01.90): Likely viral/COVID-related.
# Hyperlipidemia (E11.69): Patient immunocompromised (DM) — aggressive treatment warranted.
Plan: Paxlovid x 5 days. Hold statin. Albuterol PRN. Rest, fluids. Call if worsening SOB. Follow-up 10 days.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>09/01/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Annual Wellness Visit</td><td>ANNUAL WELLNESS VISIT — G0439
45yo female here for AWV.
Preventive:
- Cervical cancer: Pap + HPV co-test 2023. Next 2028.
- Breast cancer: Mammogram 2024. Due 2025 — order.
- Colorectal: Approaching age 45. Discussed options — will do FIT test.
- Depression: PHQ-9 = 5 (minimal).
- Diabetes eye exam: Last 2024. Due 2025 — scheduled with ophthalmology.
- Foot exam: Monofilament normal bilateral. Pedal pulses 2+.
- Shingrix: Age 45, started dose 1 today.
- Osteoporosis: Not yet due.
Vaccines: Flu, Shingrix dose 1 given.
Advance Directive: Completed.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
